_bk;t=1782137489207Note: switching to 'FETCH_HEAD'.
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207You are in 'detached HEAD' state. You can look around, make experimental
_bk;t=1782137489207changes and commit them, and you can discard any commits you make in this
_bk;t=1782137489207state without impacting any branches by switching back to a branch.
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207If you want to create a new branch to retain commits you create, you may
_bk;t=1782137489207do so (now or later) by using -c with the switch command. Example:
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207  git switch -c <new-branch-name>
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207Or undo this operation with:
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207  git switch -
_bk;t=1782137489207
_bk;t=1782137489207Turn off this advice by setting config variable advice.detachedHead to false
